          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>We have a canonical map

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>834</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>2.1.3.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         w\colon  \mathbb {G}_\mathrm {m}\to  S       \tag{2.1.3.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    
    that, on the real points, induces the inclusion of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^*]]></fr:tex> into <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}^*]]></fr:tex>.
    We have

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>835</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>2.1.3.2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         zw         = \overline {z}w         = \mathrm {Id}.       \tag{2.1.3.2}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
            <fr:p>We also have a map

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>836</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.3</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.3.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>2.1.3.3</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         N\colon  S\to \mathbb {G}_\mathrm {m}       \tag{2.1.3.3}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    that on the real points can be identified with the norm <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N_{\mathbb {C}{/}\mathbb {R}}\colon \mathbb {C}^*\to \mathbb {R}^*]]></fr:tex>.
    We have

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>837</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.4</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.4.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>2.1.3.4</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         N = z\overline {z}       \tag{2.1.3.4}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>838</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.5</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.1.3.5.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>2.1.3.5</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         N\circ  w         = (x\mapsto  x^2).       \tag{2.1.3.5}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
